en_146639_0	Joint Opposition member and former Minister, Professor G.L. Peiris has been appointed as the new Chairman of the Sri Lanka Podujana Peramuna.
en_146639_1	It has been reported that the change has been informed to the Election Commissioner.  The new party’s election symbol is a flower bud.
en_146639_2	The name of Sri Lanka Jathika Peramuna Chaired by Wimal Geeganage was changed to Ape Sri Lanka Nidahas Peramuna last April.
en_146639_3	It has now been changed to Sri Lanka Podujana Peramuna.
en_146639_4	Sagara Kariyawasam functions as the General Secretary of the new party.
en_146639_5	Sagara Kariyawasam says that his party is getting ready to contest future elections including the forthcoming local government polls.
en_146639_6	However, Party General Secretary Kariyawasam said that a top leader for the party has not yet been appointed.
